default3. Is there a sufficient level of funding for R&amp;D in the UK?default&#xa0;
default3.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAs highlighted in the NAO report ‘Research and Devel
defaultopment funding for science and technology in the UK’, the UK has had a consistently low percentage of GDP spent on R&amp;D over the last 20 years, considerably lower than most rival nation competitors in the industries ADS represents.
default&#xa0;
default3.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAs shown in Figure 2 below, since the recession, the UK has fallen behind key OECD competitors in terms of Government spending on all R&amp;D across the economy and has in fact reduced R&amp;D spending as a proportion of GDP since 2007. 
defaultThis has left the UK at default21defaultsdefaulttdefault defaultin the OECD for Government spending and support on all R&amp;D programmes.default 
