default UK still has a long way to go to reach the Europe 2020 target of 
default3%
default of GDP spent on R&amp;D, as also raised in the NAO report.
default&#xa0;
default3.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBy removing capital spend from the ring-fenced science budget, the infrastructure at which research takes place is also threatened.
default Laboratory based teaching is far more expensive than the classroom-based equivalent and with falling capital spending; science infrastructure is an easy target for universities looking to save money.
default&#xa0;
default3.5
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSMEs often face prohibitive costs to use test faciliti
defaultes for the purpose of trialling, experimenting and developing their innovative technology in real-life environments. The lack of funding spent on development in comparison to research further hinders progress in the engineering sectors 
defaultADS represents where
default the R&amp;D model they are operating under requires far greater funding for development than initial research.
default&#xa0;
default3.6
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe 1.2
default%
default minimum spend on Science and Technology (S&amp;T) in the defence budget set by the Government in the National Security through Technology Whit
defaulte Paper in February 2012 will halt the spiralling decrease in the defence S&amp;T budget over the past two decades. It is important that this figure is not treated as a target but is built upon to increase the spend on S&amp;T and ensure the UK is not left behind 
defaultby other nations investing more in the development of future equipment. 
